Uses of Package

  • Classes in <Unnamed> used by <Unnamed> 
    Class Description
    City
    City objects represent in-game cities that must be cleared of villains to win the game.
    DiceRolls
    Instances of DiceRolls represent a type of minigame the player could play to battle villains.
    Game
    A Game object is an application window containing all the components for a single game.
    GameEnvironment
    GameEnvironment objects are used by Game objects to play through the game.
    GuessNumber
    Instances of GuessNumber represent a type of minigame that the player used to battle villains.
    HealingItem
    Instances of HealingItem represent healing items that the player can obtain in the game.
    Hero
    Instances of Hero represent heroes on a team.
    Location
    The Location enumerable contains one value for each location in a city.
    MiniGame
    Instances of MiniGame represent games that the player can play to defeat villains.
    MiniGameType
    The MiniGameType enumerable contains a value for each type of minigame the player could be required to play to defeat villains.
    PaperScissorsRock
    An instance of PaperScissorsRock represents a minigame that the player can play against a villain.
    PowerUp
    PowerUp objects represent particular beneficial items that the player can obtain in the game.
    PowerUpType
    The PowerUpType enumerable contains a value for each power up in the game.
    Refreshable
    Panels which contain dynamic components should implement the Refreshable interface.
    Sector
    A Sector object represents one area which the player can visit in a city.
    SectorType
    An enumeration containing a value for each type of sector which occurs in a city.
    Team
    Instances of Team represent teams of heroes in the game.
    Villain
    Instances of the Villain class represent opponents the player will face in the game.
    VillainsLairPanel
    A VillainsLairPanel is a panel contained in the main CardLayout of the Game window.
